    "summary": "W. Martin Smid was born in The Netherlands and obtained his MD in Medicine at the University of Groningen (The Netherlands) in 1988 and his PhD in 1995. He started his medical career in 1988 as MD at the Department of Internal Medicine of the University Hospital Groningen as MD for 3 years, and until 1996 as physician for coagulation at the Haematology Department.\n\nIn 1996 he became Medical Director of the Blood Bank in Enschede. Over the years he filled positions at several Blood Bank locations as Medical Director and Division Director. During this period he successfully completed an executive MBA. Until October 2014 he was Manager Clinical Consulting at Sanquin Blood Supply region North East and responsible for the clinical interface including stem cell collection.\n\nSince 2005 he is managing director of Sanquin Consulting Services, an internationally facilitating unit of Sanquin Blood Supply, providing guidance advice services to restricted economy countries. In this function he has been involved in projects in various countries, including TA provision for PEPfAR in Zambia and Uganda, EU funded project in Turkey and currently Sri Lanka, Georgia and Suriname. As of 2000 he is advisor of the Red Cross Blood Bank at Curacao.\nHe is also acting Director of the Academic Institute for the International Development of Transfusion Medicine (IDTM), which offers a postgraduate of Management of Transfusion Medecine programme (MTM-programme). \n\nDr. Martin Smid takes part in WHO Global Blood Safety Network and Global Forum on Blood Safety and has participated in the Patient Safety and Rights project and the AfSBT Step Wise Accreditation work group. \nHe is chair of the ISBT working party on Global Blood Safety and member of the ISBT working party Blood Supply management, the AfSBT Education Committee and AfSBT standards committee and also JACIE inspector for collection.\n\nHe has contributed to over 40 international publications in the field of haemophilia, coagulation and transfusion.\n\nSpecialties: management of change and professional relations",
